Summer is here in full swing and along with the scorching temperatures comes seemingly endless sport events. Whether you’re an athlete or a spectator, it is important to protect yourself against harmful UV rays. Mopani Pharmacy suggests a few simple precautions to ensure your skin protection is optimised: Charl Weber of Mopani Pharmnacy explain that UV (A) cannot pass through glass, burns and causes skin cancer,  while UV (B) ages, causes wrinkles, sun sports, skin cancer and can pass through glass. Weber adds that sunscreen should be applied regularly, even when it’s overcast.  “About two tablespoons – 30 millilitres should be sufficient,” he said.